
make sure nvm is installed

node -v
to check current node version

nvm --version
to check current version of nvm

we can now install as many versions of node using nvm and use the required version when needed

to install version 14.20.0 use,

nvm install v14.20.0

use nvm list to see all the available node versions on the system

nvm list can show available node versions now you can change versions using,

nvm use v16.15.1

just write the version name and it changes.

=====

for installing nvm

sudo apt install curl 

curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/master/install.sh | bash

source ~/.bashrc   

=====


